Melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium-high heat and cook chicken, turning once, 6 minutes or until golden brown. Remove chicken; set aside. In same skillet add Recipe Ready Marsala Blend, and cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, 6 minutes or until liquid is almost absorbed. Sprinkle with flour and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Stir in wine and broth; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and add back chicken. Simmer 4 minutes or until sauce is thickened and chicken is thoroughly cooked.* Season, with salt and black pepper.